  "body": "**Objective** \r\nStandardize the input and output for the solidity static analysis and develop a plugin by incorporating other static analyzers in it\r\n\r\n**Implementation Detail**\r\nEach tool owner needs to develop a plugin which will expose the APIs to be used by CSSA plugin. Tool owner plugin can be of any type of available remix plugin but this should export the analysis result in a predefined format ( in JSON ). This report can be further rendered by CSSA plugin within a predefined UI format. There will also be a functionality to download the analysis report.\r\n\r\n**Possible Approaches:**\r\n\r\n**Individual analysis**\r\n\r\nIn this, we will select only one analysis tool at once to run the analysis.\r\n\r\nThis way we can do a bit more micromanagement of analysis tools individually. We can define the terminology for the analysis modules and can improve the categorization specifically. User interface can also be more specific to that one tool only.\r\n\r\n**Combined analysis**\r\n\r\nWith this, we can run the analysis using one or more than one tool at once.\r\n\r\nThis can be bring a lot of value. Our interface and corresponding UI needs to be more generic. We have to plan it smartly to present it in a user-friendly manner.\r\n\r\n**UI/UX**\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/aTmaPV5FR9noQ3w6VSkeH7e8/Untitled?node-id=0%3A1",
